<div class="content">
  <% unless @authors.empty? %>
	<table>
		<thead>
		<th><h2><%= (author_signed_in? and params[:q].blank?) ? 'Following ' : "") + pluralize(@authors.total_entries, 'Author' %></h2></th>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
		<% @authors.in_groups_of(2, false) do |authors| %> 
		  <tr>  
		    <% authors.each do |author| %>  
		    	<td>
			      <% unless author.nil? %>
							<%= image_tag "http://api.twitter.com/1/users/profile_image/#{author.username}", :class => "photo_mini" %>
		      	  <span class="name"><%= link_to author.display_name, author_path(author.username) %></span><br/>
		          <%= link_to "@#{author.username}", "http://twitter.com/#{author.username}" %>
		        <% end %>
	      	</td>
		    <% end %>  
		  </tr>  
	<% end %>
	</tbody>
	</table>
	
	<%= will_paginate @authors %>

<% else %>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="span12">
	<h2>Welcome to ScienceCard</h2>
	<p>ScienceCard allows a researcher to create and maintain a researcher profile with minimal effort. ScienceCard will list all your publications, and will automatically collect citations, bookmarks and other article-level metrics for these publications.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>To create your own ScienceCard, simply <%= link_to "sign in with Twitter", author_omniauth_authorize_path(:twitter) %>. Then optionally link your ScienceCard to your Microsoft Academic Search and/or AuthorClaim profile on the ScienceCard profile page.</li>
		<li>ScienceCard automatically lists the available ScienceCards of the people you follow on Twitter. Or search for the ScienceCards of people you know, using the search box on this page.</li>
		<li>ScienceCard automatically lists the articles written by the people you follow. Or <%= link_to "search", articles_path %> for articles written by ScienceCard authors.</li>
		<li>Once you found the ScienceCard of the person you are interested in, you can look at his publications, and how often they have been downloaded, bookmarked or cited. </li>
	</ol>
	<p>ScienceCard was started in September 2011 by Martin Fenner. Please contact him <%= link_to "@ScienceCard", "http://twitter.com/sciencecard" %> if you have questions or comments.</p>
	</div>
	</div>
<% end %>
</div>